{"key":"post-10053370","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10053370</id>\n<content>Don't buy a digital hygrometer for any price.&amp;nbsp; They're crap.&amp;nbsp; I've used ones up to $300 and they're all shit.&amp;nbsp; They can't withstand spores that are going to coat them, OR high humidity.&amp;nbsp; The transducers get clogged up with spores, and condensation forms in them as well, causing false readings.&amp;nbsp; Get a $40 mechanical hygrometer and it will last for years.&amp;nbsp; If I had a dollar for every time I've typed the above, I could buy a new PC.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10053397</next>\n<prev>10053265</prev>\n<first>10052902</first>\n<last>10056950</last>\n<when>1238179394</when>\n<utime>03/27/09 09:43 PM</utime>\n</post>"}